Welcome to The Vegan Street Food Company where everything we sell is 100% vegan also 100% Gluten Free which we know is very rare to find!

Our display is located in a prime position with visibility from both customers inside and outside the business.

name: Sweets Emporium
description:
## Lee Allsorts
We are a local sweet company that specialise in offering the very best products at 
the best possible prices. Our customer service team go above and beyond to make 
sure you, our customers, are happy from the moment of purchase right through to 
the final eaten sweet from your delivery!

This busy barbers is located in Haywards Heath. With a modern vibe this busy 
barber shop caters to various mens styles, from the classic to very modern cuts.

## The Barbers

The Barbers are open all day 7 days a week, specialising in modern
and traditional cutting.

Located in a prime location in Crawley, with a very high customer footfall.

name: Boss Gyms Eastbourne
description:
## East Sussex’s Premier Bodybuilding and Combat Sports Gym

10,000 sq ft unit - Over 60 specialist bodybuilding machines  -Dumbbells up to 70kg - Boss Fight Club providing combat instruction for all levels - Studio classes from HIIT to Booty Bands - Tanning bed - In-house barbers, masseuse and beauty therapist

name: Lanes Health Club
description:
# We’ve got a lot of smiles on the clock…
We are a group of leisure industry veterans. Fed up with the traditional hard body fitness image we decided to make a difference to the health and wellbeing of everyone. How? By creating a club that specialises in meaningful exercise based on movement and function. Or to put it another way, we’re a club that prioritises your wellbeing – and works with you to create an individual exercise programme, whatever your age, shape or goals.

name: KwikVape
description:
## VAPE SHOP IN WORTHING, UK - CHEAP & BEST SMOKING ALTERNATIVES ONLINE

Why Choose Our Vape Shop In Worthing?
We have a wide range of products and cheap smoking alternatives, suitable for beginners and advanced vapers, both on our online store and our vape shop in Worthing. Our team have extensive experience and knowledge relating to the best vape products and are on hand to help answer any vape related questions including queries about starter or advanced kits.

name: Worlds End Barber & Shop
description: Worlds End Barber Shop located outside Wivelsfield Train station, a stylish Vintage Traditional Barber & Shaving Parlour.

name: Worthing Town FC
description: Worthing Town Football Club are the exclusive tenants of Palatine Park in Worthing having moved into the newly redeveloped clubhouse in April 2012. The club now boasts over 40 teams and over 600 playing members.

name: Eastbourne Borough Football Club
description: We are Eastbourne's leading football club currently playing in the Vanarama National League South, which is the sixth tier of English football - two divisions off of the Football League. It is our ambition to become the first football club in the history of the town to play in the Football League.

name: Coffee Republic
description: A Locally owned Coffee & Food Bar, offering excellent personal service, Great Coffee, hot Chocolate and Milkshakes and Food made in house!

name: Hove Fitness & Squash
description:
### Hove Fitness & Squash

Hove Fitness & Squash opened its doors on 3rd October 2020 after three employees of the previous club on the site took on the not insubstantial challenge to provide the local community with a high quality gym, fitness and squash club which had closed in July of the same year as a direct impact of the Covid-19 pandemic.

name: Guild Care Methold House
description:
## Guild Care Head Office

Guild Care's Head Office is based at Methold House, North Street, Worthing.

A range of our day services take place here in the Guild Care Centre, and central services are based here including the Recruitment, Communications & Marketing, and Fundraising teams as well as the CEO's office.

name: Fitzalan Howard Centre
description:
## Fitzalan Howard Centre

The Fitzalan Howard Centre provides day and respite services for adults with disabilities and more complex needs on Mondays to Fridays, 9am to 4pm.

### What Fitzalan offers

Activities ranging from quiet sensory sessions to rowdy karaoke, football in the park, bargain hunting at the local market, art, cookery, and swimming
A high staff-to-client ratio, ensuring a good level of individual support
Additional support available for those people with greater needs
A long established service with a good reputation

name: Guild Care Woods Way

address.address1: Guild Care Woods Way Charity Superstore & Donation Centre

description:
## Woods Way Charity Superstore & Donation Centre

Woods Way is Guild Care's exciting, new charity superstore and donation centre in Goring-by-Sea.

name: Guild Care Littlehampton
description:
## Littlehampton Charity Superstore & Donation Centre

This store is much more than your usual charity shop. It is packed with bargains including furniture, children's clothes and toys, quirky household items, vintage and designer clothes and much more. It's easy to drop off your donations too at the same time.

name: Guild Care Greenhouse Charity Superstore
description:
## The Greenhouse Charity Superstore Worthing

The Greenhouse is much more than a charity furniture shop and warehouse. Packed with bargains from furniture, toys and books, to electrical goods, household, sports equipment, clothes, games etc. It's easy to drop off your donations too.

name: King & Queen Brighton
description:
## King & Queen Brighton
Located in the heart of Brighton city centre, the largest traditional English pub in Brighton. With two huge screens, we boast the ultimate football viewing experience with a fine range of homemade food and beers, coupled by an unbeatable atmosphere!

name: Guild Care Findon
description:
## Findon Charity Shop
One of our newest Guild Care shops. It is situated in the popular Findon Road parade. Findon Road has a wide variety of items from crafts, designer clothes and accessories to bric-a-brac, toys and books.

name: Guild Care Broadwater
description:
## Broadwater Charity Shop
Our Broadwater shop sells a wide variety of items including second-hand and new furniture, clothes, bric-a-brac and toys.

name: Guild Care Rowlands Road
description:
## Rowlands Road Charity Shop

One of our longest established shops on the outskirts of the town centre which opened over 20 years ago.

Rowlands Road has a wide variety of white goods (which are PAT tested) for sale, plus a range of home furniture and a large selection of £1 bargains. It also has a quiet designated reading area to enable you to take your time to browse through the extensive collection of books available.

name: Guild Care South Farm Road
description:
## South Farm Road Charity Shop

Located along South Farm Road parade, this shop sells a range of bric-a-brac, clothes and household goods.

name: Guild Care Strand Left
description:
Strand Charity Shops

We now have two charity shops situated on the Strand Parade. There’s a lot to offer in both shops especially if you are book buff. The bookshop bazaar is very popular with locals and passing commuters. There’s also lots of clothing, accessories, bric-a-brac, children's toys and furniture.

name: Guild Care Strand Right
description:
## Strand Charity Shops

We now have two charity shops situated on the Strand Parade. There’s a lot to offer in both shops especially if you are book buff. The bookshop bazaar is very popular with locals and passing commuters. There’s also lots of clothing, accessories, bric-a-brac, children's toys and furniture.

name: Guild Care Warwick Street
description:
## Warwick Street Charity Shop

Situated on the popular shopping thoroughfare of Warwick Street, this is one of Guild Care’s newest charity shop, opened in 2016.

Warwick Street charity shop is now the go to destination for more retro and vintage goods, but you’ll also find the usual bric-a-brac, clothes, books and so on.

name: Lewes Football Club
description:
## The Dripping Pan

Few football clubs in the UK, let alone Europe, can boast of playing at the same venue for over 135 years as Lewes Football Club can. Better still, our ground was recently voted No.1 in the “British Football’s Greatest Grounds” book. Eat your heart out Anfield.

name: Littlehampton Golf
description:
## Littlehampton Golf
Littlehampton Golf Club was founded in 1889, and is the only Links golf course in West Sussex and was recently described in GOLF NEWS as ‘Sussex’s Hidden Gem of a Links’. The 18 hole par 70 course is never the same from one day to the next as the changing wind conditions make each hole set up differently from round to round.

name: St Barnabas House Storrington
description: This busy and well-supported charity shop is one of the main focal points for the village. The local residents very generously donate all of the items for sale in the shop, and there are good quality clothes, shoes, handbags and bric-a-brac to choose from.

name: St Barnabas House Lyons Farm
description: Our newest shop is open at Lyons Farm Retail Park, next to Sainsbury’s. Filled to the brim with lots of exciting stock. Clothes, shoes, handbags, accessories, bric-a-brac, games, toys, and books – there is something for everyone.

name: St Barnabas House Durrington
description: Our Durrington charity shop is one of our largest shops. We have a huge range of furniture, bric-a-brac and homeware as well as ladieswear, menswear and childrenswear. The shop can also collect and deliver large items of furniture.

name: St Barnabas House Wick
description: One of our largest shops, Wick is a mini department store with something for everyone – good quality furniture, white goods, bric-a-brac, toys, games and books. Also clothing for ladies, gents and children, including many High Street brands at low prices. The shop can also collect and deliver large items of furniture.

name: Guild Care Haviland House
description:
## Haviland House Dementia Care Home in Worthing, West Sussex
Haviland House is a specialist dementia care home located at the foot of the South Downs in Goring, West Sussex. It was purpose built in 2015 to fulfil the needs of residents living with different stages of dementia.

In 2019 Haviland House was a ‘Best Dementia Care Home’ finalist in the National Dementia Care Awards and the home’s Health & Wellbeing Coordinator won the National Activity Providers Association’s ‘Best Activity Coordinator’ award.

name: Guild Care Caer Gwent
description:
## Caer Gwent Nursing Care Home in Worthing, West Sussex
Caer Gwent combines superb residential living with 24-hour expert nursing care, supporting individuals with complex health conditions, particularly focusing on palliative (i.e. end of life) support.

Opened in 1988 by the Earl of March, Caer Gwent is an elegant care home set in a quiet residential area of Worthing. Our home features spacious and airy surroundings, beautiful furnishings and well-tended landscaped gardens.

name: Guild Care Linfield House
description:
## Linfield House Nursing Care Home in Worthing, West Sussex
Linfield House is a residential and nursing care home that includes two dementia suites. We promote independent living, providing residents with the support and person-centred care that they need to flourish.

In the 15 years that we have owned and run Linfield House, it has successfully supported couples, particularly when one has dementia and one does not.

name: Hope Hive
description:
Hope Hive is a family venue where families can be together, connect with others, play, learn and create. 

We are passionate about supporting families to thrive with over 25 years of experience supporting young children in their growth and development.

name: Chestnut Tree House Havant
description:
Situated in West Street, Havant is our largest furniture shop and can arrange furniture collection and deliveries. 

We also stock clothing, accessories, bric-a-brac, small electricals, homewares, toys and games.

name: Chestnut Tree House Bognor
description:
We stock a varied range of quality ladieswear and accessories, menswear and also children’s clothes and toys. 

The Bridal Department on the first floor sells a gorgeous range of new and pre-loved wedding dresses.

name: Tonbridge Angels FC
description: Tonbridge Football Club were formed in October 1947 following the suggestion of local businessman and founder chairman Mr. Herbert Portch, and were one of four clubs to be elected to the Southern League for the 1948-49 season.

name: St Barnabas Rowlands Road
description: Set in a parade of independent shops, our sells good quality ladieswear, menswear, childrenswear and accessories. The Wedding Boutique is situated upstairs and stocks a range of new and pre-loved wedding dresses, bridal accessories, bridesmaids and prom dresses.

name: St Barnabas House Shoreham
description: Our St Barnabas House shop in Shoreham High Street, sells a range of items including clothing, accessories, shoes, handbags, bric-a-brac and books. There is also a children’s corner selling clothes, toys and games. The shop is open 7 days a week.

name: St Barnabas House Littlehampton
description: Situated in Anchor Springs, just off the High Street, the shop sells a large selection of ladies and menswear, shoes, bags, accessories, curtains, bed linen, children’s toys, games and puzzles. It also stocks a range of new pet goods for your furry friends.

name: Body Happy Lewes
description: Body Happy is a supportive, encouraging community of people in Lewes who are all proud to help you achieve your goals and stay fit, happy and healthy for life.

name: Guild Care Crawley
description: This is a brand new retail unit for Guild Care right in the heart of Crawley town centre.

name: Guildbourne Centre
description: Worthings only town centre shopping mall. With a variety of local and national businesses in side and high footfall. This is a fantastic location to boost your business.

name: Guild Care Hove
description: We are excited to confirm that a new Guild Care charity shop is now open in Hove! We sell an exciting range of high quality goods such as clothing, accessories, toys, bric-a-brac, homeware, books, DVD's and more. Visit us today to shop or donate.
